      "id": "vad",
      "type": "automated_step",
      "slug": "vad",
      "position": { "x": 340, "y": 160 },
      "data": {
        "type": "automated_step",
        "label": "VAD filter",
        "description": "Borrows the uploaded WAV from Start via `{{ start.audio }}` (compiler stages it via StoragePath, runner resolves to a local path). Reads it with the stdlib `wave` module, runs a simple energy-gate VAD over 30 ms frames (pure-Python `audioop` RMS — swap webrtcvad/silero for production), and re-emits ONLY the voiced frames as raw 16-bit PCM over the Data/Out channel `speech` (~100 ms per write). The bulk audio bytes flow out-of-band over the JetStream datastream transport — they NEVER enter the net marking; the net sees only the channel's open + close (docs/25).",
        "channels": [
          {
            "name": "speech",
            "direction": "out",
            "plane": "data",
            "element": { "type": "binary", "content_type": "audio/L16" }
          }
        ],
        "executionSpec": {
          "backendType": "python",
          "entrypoint": "main.py",
          "config": {
            "python": "python3",
            "requirements": [],
            "virtualenv": false,
            "sdk": true,
            "inherit_env": true,
            "env": {}
          }
        },
        "output": {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "VAD stats",
          "fields": [
            { "name": "frames_total", "label": "Frames total", "kind": "number" },
            { "name": "frames_voiced", "label": "Frames voiced", "kind": "number" },
            { "name": "sample_rate", "label": "Sample rate", "kind": "number" }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "transcribe",
      "type": "automated_step",
      "slug": "transcribe",
      "position": { "x": 660, "y": 160 },
      "data": {
        "type": "automated_step",
        "label": "Transcribe (faster-whisper)",
        "description": "Declares a Data/In channel `speech` wired from the VAD step's open handle. `aithericon.stream('speech')` drains the out-of-band voiced-audio byte stream (starting EARLY, while the VAD step is still producing), reassembles the raw 16-bit PCM, and runs faster-whisper (`tiny`, CPU/int8) over it. Sets the recognized text as `transcript`. LIVE-ONLY: first run pip-installs faster-whisper (ctranslate2/numpy) and downloads the `tiny` model (~75 MB) into the venv/HF cache — slow + network-dependent, exceeds the 60 s `mekhan test` cap on a cold run.",
        "channels": [
          {
            "name": "speech",
            "direction": "in",
            "plane": "data",
            "element": { "type": "binary", "content_type": "audio/L16" }
          }
        ],
        "executionSpec": {
          "backendType": "python",
          "entrypoint": "main.py",
          "config": {
            "python": "python3",
            "requirements": ["faster-whisper", "numpy"],
            "virtualenv": true,
            "sdk": true,
            "inherit_env": true,
            "env": {}
          }
        },
        "output": {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Transcript",
          "fields": [
            { "name": "transcript", "label": "Transcript", "kind": "text" },
            { "name": "seconds", "label": "Audio seconds", "kind": "number" }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
